# Memory

Session-scratch for Claude. What Claude should remember between turns or across sessions, without polluting versioned docs.

## What lives here

* Open questions the team is still working on.
* Mid-session decisions too small to be an ADR but too load-bearing to lose.
* Running TODOs Claude should pick up next time.
* Notes about *context* that don't belong in code or docs.

## What doesn't

* Anything that's a spec or a decision — that goes in `../docs/` (see [README](../docs/README.md)).
* Secrets — this folder is committed like any other.
* Long-form research — that goes in `../docs/research/`.

## Conventions

* Files are free-form Markdown.
* If a memory outgrows this folder (large, structured, referenced), promote it to a doc and delete the memory note.
* This folder is intentionally in the repo so every contributor sees the same "what's in Claude's head" state.
